[2026-07-06] BUGFIX — sign-up 42501 (RLS) on the profiles insert
  What happened: real device test hit `PostgrestException(...new row violates
    row-level security policy for table "profiles"..., code: 42501)` right after
    signUp(). Root cause: the Supabase project has "Confirm email" ON, so
    auth.signUp() returns a user but NO session until the confirmation link is
    clicked — the profiles INSERT that follows in AuthController.signUp() has no
    access_token, so `auth.uid()` is null server-side and the
    `auth.uid() = user_id` RLS policy rejects it.
  Decision (user): disable "Confirm email" in the Supabase dashboard
    (Authentication → Providers → Email) rather than restructure the code to
    defer profile-row creation until post-confirmation. No app code changed for
    this fix — it's a dashboard setting only. Re-enable before production launch
    (and if re-enabled, the profiles-insert-on-signUp flow will need revisiting).

