[2026-07-09] BUILD FIX (record pkg) + real upload-error surfacing + backend media spec
  1) Android build was failing at kernel_snapshot_program:
       record_linux 0.7.2 doesn't implement record_platform_interface 1.6.0
       (missing startStream; hasPermission signature mismatch).
     Even though record_linux is Linux-only and irrelevant to Android, Flutter
     compiles the whole dep graph, so it broke the build.
     FIX: bumped `record: ^5.1.2` -> `^7.1.1` in pubspec.yaml, which resolves a
     consistent set (record_linux 2.1.1 + record_platform_interface 2.1.0).
     VoiceRecorderService needed no code change (API compatible).
     Verified: `flutter build apk --debug` -> SUCCESS.
  2) Root-caused the on-device "Could not add photo — try again." error.
     Device log showed FaceDetectorV2Jni start/end (pick + ML Kit face check
     BOTH worked, face found) — the failure was in the upload step.
     Probed the live project directly:
       GET  /storage/v1/bucket                 -> []   (ZERO buckets exist)
       POST /storage/v1/object/avatars/<path>  -> {"statusCode":"404",
                                                   "error":"Bucket not found"}
     So: no Storage buckets have been created in the Supabase project at all.
     (Note: the storage `list` endpoint returns [] for a nonexistent bucket
     rather than 404 — misleading. The upload probe is the reliable check.)
  3) MY BUG, fixed: every media catch block was `catch (_)` and swallowed the
     real error, so the UI only ever said "try again" and the true cause was
     invisible. Added:
       - lib/shared/data/profile_photo_repository.dart: MediaUploadException
         (message + isMissingBucket) and mapStorageError(error, bucket) which
         maps StorageException 404/"bucket" -> "Storage bucket "X" does not
         exist. Create it in the Supabase dashboard.", 403/RLS -> a policy
         message, else "Upload failed: <msg>".
       - uploadPhoto() and ChatRepository._uploadPrivate() now wrap the
         uploadBinary/createSignedUrl calls and throw MediaUploadException.
       - All 5 UI call sites (onboarding avatar + gallery, profile add +
         change-avatar, chat attach + voice) now catch MediaUploadException
         and show e.message; generic catches now interpolate the real error
         instead of discarding it.
  4) NEW DOC for the backend team:
       app doctumant/BACKEND_MEDIA_REQUIREMENTS.md
     Complete hand-off spec for the media/image system: the 5 exact bucket
     names + public/private, copy-paste Storage RLS SQL (incl. an
     is_conversation_participant() SECURITY DEFINER helper), the exact client
     upload contract (paths, MIME types, compression caps, signed-URL TTL),
     the DB constraints we rely on, a requested `moderate-image` edge-function
     contract (safe/isHuman/categories, profile-vs-chat rules, and a strong
     recommendation to run it as a storage webhook rather than client-invoked
     so it can't be bypassed), the conversations-auto-create blocker, an error
     contract, an acceptance checklist, and 7 open questions (signed-URL
     expiry strategy, primary-photo auto-promotion, max photo count 4 vs 6,
     chat-files-vs-chat-videos naming, location lat/lng, etc.).
  Verified: `flutter analyze` -> No issues found (2 pre-existing false-positive
    info lints). `flutter test` -> All tests passed (2).
  STILL BLOCKED on the user/backend creating the 5 buckets + policies; until
    then every upload fails, but now with an accurate on-screen reason.

[2026-07-09] GROUP A — wire up already-built repository code that no UI called
  Scope: the 8 "quick win" items from FRONTEND_REMAINING.md that needed zero
    new backend — the repository methods existed but nothing invoked them.
    7 of 8 done; 1 turned out to be blocked (see A6).

  PRE-FLIGHT CHECK (important): probed the live project before starting, since
    an earlier summary of mine had claimed `reports` was live. It is NOT:
      reports                 -> HTTP 404   (DOES NOT EXIST)
      profile_views           -> HTTP 200
      likes / matches         -> HTTP 200
      call_logs               -> HTTP 200
      message_reactions       -> HTTP 200
      notification_preferences-> HTTP 200
    So A6 was dropped, and A7's "Views" stat had to change (see below).

  A1 — Chat read receipts (DONE)
    - chat_repository.dart: added markManyAsRead(ids) — a single upsert into
      `message_reads` with onConflict:'message_id,user_id', ignoreDuplicates,
      instead of N round-trips.
    - chat_screen.dart: new _markIncomingRead(convoId) marks every message
      from the other participant read. Called (a) once after the initial
      history load (post-frame), and (b) on every realtime inbound message.
      A `_markedRead` Set de-dupes within the session; on failure the ids are
      removed from it so a later attempt can retry.
    - Effect: the other side's single-check now actually becomes a double-check.

  A2 — Chat reactions are now VISIBLE (DONE)
    - Previously write-only: addReaction() was called on long-press but the
      app never read `message_reactions` back, so reactions never appeared.
    - chat_repository.dart: added reactionsFor(messageIds) (inFilter query).
    - repositories.dart: new reactionsProvider(conversationId) which depends on
      messagesProvider and fetches reactions for the loaded message ids.
    - chat_screen.dart: bubbles are now wrapped in a Column with reaction chips
      underneath. Chips group by emoji with a count ("❤️ 3"); a chip you
      contributed to is outlined in pink and tapping it calls removeReaction()
      (which existed and had never been called from anywhere).
    - profile_tile.dart: added an `onLongPress` param (needed by A4 too).

  A3 — Calls tab renders real call_logs (DONE)
    - Was a hardcoded EmptyView("No calls yet.") that read nothing, while
      CallRepository.getCallHistory() sat unused.
    - repositories.dart: new callHistoryProvider — fans out getCallHistory()
      across every conversation, merges, sorts by started_at desc.
    - messages_screen.dart: real _callsTab() with per-row direction icon
      (outgoing/incoming/missed), audio-vs-video icon, duration ("2m 14s") or
      status, partner avatar+name resolved from conversationsProvider, relative
      timestamp, pull-to-refresh, and loading/empty/error states.
    - Rows are read-only — placing a call still needs WebRTC (not built).

  A4 — Unmatch / Block now reachable (DONE)
    - MatchRepository.unmatch()/block() existed with no UI entry point.
    - repositories.dart: new myMatchRowsProvider — matchesProvider only exposes
      the partner's Profile, but unmatch/block key off the match id, so the raw
      `matches` rows are needed to resolve profile -> match.
    - likes_screen.dart (Matches tab): long-press a match -> action sheet
      (Unmatch / Block) -> typed confirmation dialog -> repository call ->
      invalidates matchesProvider + myMatchRowsProvider + conversationsProvider.
      Both are soft status UPDATEs; the row is never deleted.

  A5 — Settings notification toggles are REAL (DONE)
    - getPreferences()/updatePreferences() existed, never called. The section
      was 4 fake setState switches.
    - repositories.dart: new notificationPreferencesProvider.
    - settings_screen.dart: replaced with the actual 8 columns of
      `notification_preferences` — push_enabled, email_enabled, and the 6
      per-category toggles (likes/matches/messages/calls/profile views/
      marketing). Each flip PATCHes immediately; the provider is invalidated
      afterwards either way so the switches always reflect the server rather
